The paper deals with the problem of coded caching over fading channels, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper proposes an online delivery scheme that combines joint scheduling and power control for the fading broadcast channel, as well as congestion control for ensuring the optimal long-term average performance, which involves system-level optimization and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions simulations, which suggests that the paper may involve some form of data analysis or machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the design and analysis of an algorithm, which suggests that it may fall under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS).
